page.enlisting:
▪ Breakdown of the 131 turnover actions include 34 transfers out of the agency, 3 dismissals, 1 disability separation, 5 probationary separations, 73 resignations, 12 retirements, and 3 in the “other” category occurring during this reporting period. ▪ An agency-wide Succession Planning Committee has identified necessary strategies and steps for employee development, which will include mission critical and key roles in DOR. ▪ DOR will continue to collaborate with other state agencies to identify potential opportunities to improve retention. DOR had a lead role in producing a report for the Governor with recommendations for reducing turnover and retaining employees. ▪ DOR will continue to gather and assess data collected through the agency’s standardized agency exit survey (deployed in 2007) and direct resources to address areas of high turnover. ▪ An agency-wide action committee was formed in 2006 and is currently working to identify retention opportunities and strategies. ▪ Over 130 candidates attended the agency’s on-site Career Open House, which resulted in 9 new hires.
